'''Norman M. Scott''' was a [[Canadian]] [[figure skater]] who competed in both [[single skating]] and [[pair skating]]. His pairs partner was [[Jeanne Chevalier]]. As a single skater, he is the 1914 and 1920 [[Canadian Figure Skating Championships|Canadian champion]]. He and Chevalier won the 1914 Canadian pairs title. Scott was part of the four teams that won the silver medal in the Canadian fours championships in 1913.
Scott also competed in the United States and won the first [[United States Figure Skating Championships]] in both singles and pairs.
